While The Writer’s Diet is as sleek and concise as the writing ideals contained within, this slim volume packs a powerful punch. With Sword’s coaching writers of all levels can strengthen and tone their sentences with the stroke of a pen or the click of a mouse. As with any fitness routine, adhering to the rules requires energy and vigilance. The results, however, will speak for themselves.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEnglish languagevProblems, exercises, etc.xStyle. 0aEnglish languagexProblems, exercises, etcxStyle. 0aEnglish languagexRhetoric. 0aEnglish languagexStylevProblems, exercises, etc. 0aEnglish languagexStyle. 0aEnglish languagexWritten English. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / General.2bisacsh  aprose, prosody, creative writing, writer, sentence, paragraph, parts of speech, research, handbook, guidebook, verbal, communication, written, language, preposition, verb, adverb, noun, adjective, shakespeare, dickinson, martin luther king jr, john mcphee, as byatt, richard dawkins, close readings, english, college, university, textbook.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311071098440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226352039423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226352039/original  a978-3-11-071098-4  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles